"use strict";(self.webpackChunkhalt_website=self.webpackChunkhalt_website||[]).push([[24143],{58580:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"tag":{"label":"rat","permalink":"/docs/tags/rat","allTagsPath":"/docs/tags","count":15,"items":[{"id":"Rats/getting-started/rat-care-guide","title":"A Comprehensive Guide to Rat Care","description":"Rats are intelligent, social, and engaging pets that bring a unique joy to any home. To ensure they live long, happy, and healthy lives, it\u2019s essential to understand and meet their specific needs. This guide provides a comprehensive overview of daily and weekly care routines for your pet rats.","permalink":"/docs/Rats/getting-started/rat-care-guide"},{"id":"Rats/breeds-and-genetics/rat-variety-guide","title":"A Guide to Fancy Rat Varieties","description":"Welcome to the colorful world of fancy rats! Through selective breeding, pet rats have been developed in a stunning array of colors, coat types, and markings. While these varieties are fascinating,...","permalink":"/docs/Rats/breeds-and-genetics/rat-variety-guide"},{"id":"Rats/getting-started/rat-nutrition-guide","title":"A Guide to Proper Rat Nutrition","description":"Proper nutrition is the cornerstone of your pet rat\'s health and longevity. As omnivores, rats have specific dietary needs that must be met to prevent obesity, nutritional deficiencies, and other...","permalink":"/docs/Rats/getting-started/rat-nutrition-guide"},{"id":"Rats/illnesses-and-conditions/rat-respiratory-infections-uris-guide","title":"A Guide to Respiratory Infections (URIs) in Rats","description":"Respiratory illness is one of the most common health issues affecting pet rats. Nearly all domestic rats are carriers of Mycoplasma pulmonis, the primary bacterium responsible for these infections...","permalink":"/docs/Rats/illnesses-and-conditions/rat-respiratory-infections-uris-guide"},{"id":"Rats/health-and-wellness/rat-introductions","title":"A Guide to Safe and Successful Rat Introductions","description":"Introducing a new rat to your existing group (or \'mischief\') is an exciting step, but it must be handled with care and patience. Rats are territorial and have complex social hierarchies. A proper...","permalink":"/docs/Rats/health-and-wellness/rat-introductions"},{"id":"Rats/getting-started/the-ideal-rat-habitat-guide","title":"Creating the Ideal Habitat for Your Pet Rats","description":"A well-designed habitat is crucial for the health, happiness, and safety of your pet rats. As active, intelligent, and social creatures, they need a space that supports their natural behaviors like...","permalink":"/docs/Rats/getting-started/the-ideal-rat-habitat-guide"},{"id":"Rats/illnesses-and-conditions/diabetes-in-rats","title":"Diabetes in Rats","description":"Diabetes Mellitus is a condition in which the body either fails to produce enough insulin or cannot use it effectively, resulting in persistently high blood sugar (hyperglycemia). While not common in pet rats, it does occur \u2014 particularly in older or overweight individuals \u2014 and requires prompt veterinary attention and a committed management plan. Understanding the signs, how diagnosis works, and what treatment looks like can make a significant difference for an affected rat 1.","permalink":"/docs/Rats/illnesses-and-conditions/diabetes-in-rats"},{"id":"Rats/getting-started/essential-rat-supplies","title":"Essential Rat Supplies","description":"Bringing pet rats home requires some preparation. Rats are intelligent, social animals with specific needs, and having the right supplies in place before they arrive will make the transition much smoother for both you and your new companions. This guide covers everything you need to set up a safe, comfortable, and enriching home for your rats.","permalink":"/docs/Rats/getting-started/essential-rat-supplies"},{"id":"Rats/getting-started/is-a-rat-right-for-me","title":"Is a Rat Right for Me and My Family?","description":"Rats are among the most intelligent, affectionate, and interactive small pets you can keep. They learn their names, come when called, enjoy being held and carried, and form genuine bonds with their...","permalink":"/docs/Rats/getting-started/is-a-rat-right-for-me"},{"id":"Rats/illnesses-and-conditions/mycoplasma-in-rats","title":"Mycoplasma in Rats: An Essential Guide","description":"If you\'re a rat owner, you\'ve likely heard the term \'myco.\' Mycoplasma pulmonis is a species of bacteria that is the primary cause of chronic respiratory disease (CRD) in pet rats. It\'s a pervasive...","permalink":"/docs/Rats/illnesses-and-conditions/mycoplasma-in-rats"},{"id":"Rats/illnesses-and-conditions/parasites-in-rats","title":"Parasites in Pet Rats","description":"Parasites are a relatively common health concern in pet rats and can affect even well-cared-for animals. Most infestations are highly treatable when caught early. This guide explains the types of parasites rats can carry, how to recognize them, how to treat them safely, and how to prevent future infestations.","permalink":"/docs/Rats/illnesses-and-conditions/parasites-in-rats"},{"id":"Rats/health-and-wellness/rat-dental-care","title":"Rat Dental Care Guide","description":"Dental health is one of the most important \u2014 and most overlooked \u2014 aspects of rat care. Because rat incisors grow continuously throughout life, they must wear down properly to prevent serious complications. A rat with dental problems will struggle to eat, lose weight rapidly, and can deteriorate quickly. Understanding how rat teeth work and how to support healthy dental wear is essential for every rat owner.","permalink":"/docs/Rats/health-and-wellness/rat-dental-care"},{"id":"Rats/breeds-and-genetics/rat-sexing-guide","title":"Rat Sexing Guide: How to Identify Male and Female Rats at Different Ages","description":"Correctly sexing rats is essential to prevent accidental litters and ensure proper housing. Rats can reproduce very young, and misidentification is one of the most common causes of surprise...","permalink":"/docs/Rats/breeds-and-genetics/rat-sexing-guide"},{"id":"Rats/getting-started/rat-treat-guide","title":"Rat Treat Guide","description":"This guide is meant to help you quickly check whether a food is generally safe as a treat for your rats. Research on rat nutrition is limited, so some guidance is based on related species or...","permalink":"/docs/Rats/getting-started/rat-treat-guide"},{"id":"Rats/health-and-wellness/understanding-rat-behavior","title":"Understanding Rat Behavior: A Guide for Owners","description":"Rats are intelligent, social, and emotionally complex animals. Understanding their natural behaviors and unique ways of communicating is key to building a strong bond and providing them with the best...","permalink":"/docs/Rats/health-and-wellness/understanding-rat-behavior"}],"unlisted":false}}')}}]);